# TOON (Token-Oriented Object Notation)

purpose{statement}:
+Define a compact, agent-optimized data format that reduces token overhead compared to JSON while remaining fully convertible.
+
+core_problem{summary}:
+JSON carries repeated syntax and key names that inflate token usage for LLMs (quotes, braces, commas, repeated keys).
+
+solution{summary}:
+TOON declares a schema once and represents uniform arrays as tables with rows inheriting that schema.
+
+principles[5]{name, description}:
+Declare Schema Once, Header defines columns for all rows
+Tabular Data Representation, Uniform arrays become tables
+Minimal Syntax, No quotes/braces; commas only separate values
+Explicit Counts, [N] declares expected row count
+Indentation for Hierarchy, Nested structures use indentation
+
+example[1]{format, content}:
+JSON, {"files":[{"path":"README.md","type":"md","line_count":526},{"path":"index.js","type":"js","line_count":42}]}
+
+example_toon[1]{format, content}:
+TOON, files[2]{path,type,line_count}:
+README.md, md, 526
+index.js, js, 42
+
+impact[3]{metric, json, toon, savings}:
+Estimated Tokens, ~2800, ~1200, ~57%
+Lines of Code, 100+, ~50, ~50%
+Agent Parse Time, Full JSON parse, Direct table scan, ~70%
+
+agent_usage[4]{step, description}:
+Pattern Recognition, Header reveals table schema and row count
+Efficient Querying, Scan a column for a value
+Memory Efficiency, Fewer tokens means more task context
+Predictable Structure, Count + schema prevents malformed data
+
+json_relation{statement}:
+TOON and JSON are isomorphic: convert between them without data loss.
+
+tradeoffs[2]{format, best_when}:
+TOON, Uniform arrays and AI-first consumption
+JSON, Human editing or complex, irregular nesting
+
+implementation_path[4]{source, view, example_json, example_toon}:
+JSON, TOON, INDEX.json, INDEX.toon
+JSON, TOON, AGENTS.json, AGENTS.toon
+Markdown, TOON, TODO.md, TODO.toon
+Markdown, TOON, BACKLOG.md, BACKLOG.toon

+why_it_matters[4]{benefit, detail}:
+More Context, Token savings free space for reasoning
+Faster Navigation, Agents scan tables quickly
+Lower Costs, Fewer tokens per session
+Clear Interfaces, Separate human vs agent formats
